[32;1m[1;3mI have analyzed the patch and the codebase of the older version. The test method "shouldAddMultipleContentLanguage" does not exist in the older version, but the context around the last test method is the same and stable enough to add this new test method directly after it.

I have crafted the following patch for the older version ref 7460be617b6fc5486cea7a8274426cf18d8c83a8:

```diff
--- a/spring-test/src/test/java/org/springframework/mock/web/MockHttpServletResponseTests.java
+++ b/spring-test/src/test/java/org/springframework/mock/web/MockHttpServletResponseTests.java
@@ -630,6 +630,14 @@
 		contentTypeHeader = response.getHeader(CONTENT_TYPE);
 		assertThat(contentTypeHeader).isEqualTo("text/plain");
 	}

+	@Test // gh-34488
+	void shouldAddMultipleContentLanguage() {
+		response.addHeader("Content-Language", "en");
+		response.addHeader("Content-Language", "fr");
+		assertThat(response.getHeaders("Content-Language")).contains("en", "fr");
+		assertThat(response.getLocale()).isEqualTo(Locale.ENGLISH);
+	}
 
 }
```

